This paper is about a software engineering technique, specifically impact analysis, which is concerned with understanding the effects of changes to software systems. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses program dependencies, which are a key aspect of programming languages and compilers, suggesting cs.PL (Programming Languages) as a possible category. The use of open source repositories and data mining suggests cs.SD (Software Development) as another possible category. The paper also discusses heuristics, which are a form of machine learning, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the precision and recall of the impact analysis technique, which are metrics commonly used in evaluation studies, suggesting cs.CR (Computing Research) as a possible category.
